# Cursor rules

Use pnpm for package management.
Install dependencies with `pnpm install`.
Run lint with `pnpm lint`.
Run coverage with `jest --coverage`.
Format with `eslint --fix`.
Use single quotes for strings.
Use 2 spaces for indentation.
Tests live in `__tests__/` folders.
This project is CommonJS.
Start the dev server with `npm start`.
CI config lives at `.circleci/config.yml`.
Prefer TypeScript for application code.
Keep React components focused and small.
Utility helpers live in `src/utils/`.
Avoid committing generated output.
Review package.json before adding scripts.
Commit style has no convention.
Write clear PR descriptions.
Prefer explicit names over abbreviations.
Keep comments focused on surprising behavior.
Ask before changing dependency versions.
Do not introduce unrelated formatting churn.
Keep changes scoped to the task.
Use existing directories before adding new ones.
Favor simple functions over clever abstractions.
Run checks before requesting review.
Document manual testing in PRs.
Avoid broad refactors in feature branches.
Use accessible labels for interactive UI.
Prefer named exports for shared utilities.
Do not duplicate business logic.
Keep imports ordered by source.
Treat linter warnings as actionable.
Use project scripts instead of global tools.
Check the actual package manager field.
Preserve public APIs unless requested.
Keep benchmark fixtures deterministic.
